view.name: 311 Explorer
view.description:
311 Explorer is a web-based mapping tool that uses the Cityâ€™s open data information to search, filter, and display 311 service requests on public property.  You will be able to:

View the various types of service requests on public property that have been generated in a neighborhood, ward or across the city, see the status of service requests, use the map or charts for analysis of neighbourhoods

columns.name: Ticket Number
columns.description: The unique identifier (number)  for the service request.

columns.name: Date Created
columns.description: The date and time the service request was first submitted.

columns.name: Date Closed
columns.description: The date the service request was acted upon. The appropriate City department has investigated the concern and identified steps to resolve your request. Action for resolving the issue may be deferred as work may be dependant on priority and weather conditions or your issue has been closed due to lack of information including contact details.

columns.name: Request Status
columns.description: The current state or condition that the ticket is in.

columns.name: Status Detail
columns.description: Describes the state or progression through the life cycle of the service request.

columns.name: Service Category
columns.description: The type of service.

columns.name: Service Details
columns.description: Provides a general description of the service request.

columns.name: Business Unit
columns.description: The business area that is responsible for the service.

columns.name: Neighbourhood
columns.description: The City neighbourhood where the service is located.

columns.name: Community League
columns.description: The Community League associated with the location of the service. (If applicable)

columns.name: Ward
columns.description: The City Ward associated with the location.

columns.name: Address
columns.description: The location of the service request.

columns.name: Lat
columns.description: Horizontal Geographic Coordinate

columns.name: Long
columns.description: Vertical Geographic Coordinate

columns.name: Location
columns.description: Spatial coordinates for the location of the issue that has been identified.

columns.name: Ticket Source
columns.description: The channel or method in which the service request was initiated. Examples will include telephone, 311 app or email.

columns.name: Calendar Year
columns.description: Year when Service Ticket was created.

columns.name: Count
columns.description: Number of service requests - usually 1. To be used for reporting purposes.

columns.name: Posse_Number
columns.description: Unique Identifier generated by POSSE

columns.name: Transit_Ref_Number
columns.description: A ticket number from any Transit application

General Information.Purpose: The dataset is comprised of 311 service requests which are mapped using a geo location  tool.  The user is able sort information based on location, ward, neighbourhood, and service category.
